<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="b1947_03_28_an_AyerAlfredJules"><teiHeader><fileDesc> <titleStmt> <title>Von <persName key="WittgensteinLudwig" role="sender" full="yes">Ludwig Wittgenstein</persName> an <persName key="AyerAlfredJules" role="recipient" full="yes">Alfred Jules Ayer</persName>, 28. 3. 1947</title> <author>Wittgenstein, Ludwig</author> </titleStmt> <editionStmt n="bw2"> <edition>2. Auflage</edition> </editionStmt> <publicationStmt> <p>Ludwig Wittgenstein: Gesamtbriefwechsel, 2. Auflage</p> </publicationStmt> <sourceDesc default="false"> <p>Abschrift McGuinness.</p> </sourceDesc> </fileDesc><encodingDesc><p>TEI P5</p></encodingDesc><revisionDesc><list type="simple"><item>2010/05/15: Added to the collection</item><item>2018/12: Added to Innsbruck Correspondence Edition</item></list></revisionDesc></teiHeader><text><body><div org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete" type="transcript"> <div type="address" org="uniform" sample="complete" part="N"> <p rend="right">28.3.47</p> </div> <div type="maintext" org="uniform" sample="complete" part="N"> <p rend="left">Dear Professor Ayer,</p> <p rend="indent">Thank you for your letter of March 25<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. I was glad to read that you had no intention to travesty my work, &amp; if this is so, I know you will in future not even seem to have this intention. The sincere wish to be fair to a man &amp; not to do him an injustice, even if the writer were clumsy - which I have not reason to believe you are - cannot easily be misread; unless the reader is blind, which I hope Iâ€™m not.</p> </div> <div type="salute" org="uniform" sample="complete" part="N"> <p rend="indent">Yours sincerely </p> <p rend="indent">L. Wittgenstein </p> </div> </div></body></text></TEI>